Subject: CVE-2024-29070: Apache StreamPark: session not invalidated after
 logout 

Severity: moderate

Affected versions:

- Apache StreamPark 1.0.0 before 2.1.4

Description:

On versions before 2.1.4,Â session is not invalidated after logout. When the user logged in successfully, the Backend service returns "Authorization" as the front-end authentication credential. "Authorization" can still initiate requests and access data even after logout.

Mitigation:

all users should upgrade to 2.1.4

Credit:

L0ne1y (reporter)

